## File Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `ProjectCard.jsx`, `FadeIn.jsx`)
- **Pages**: lowercase with `.jsx` (e.g., `page.jsx`, `layout.jsx`)
- **Styles**: Component name + `.scss` (e.g., `ProjectCard.scss`, `Projects.scss`)
- **Data files**: camelCase + `Data.js` (e.g., `projectsData.js`, `skillsData.js`)
- **Utilities**: camelCase (e.g., `projects.js`)

## Import Patterns

### Path Aliases
- Use `@/` prefix for src directory imports (configured in jsconfig.json)
- Example: `import { ProjectCard } from "@/components"`
- Example: `import projectsData from "@/data/projectsData"`

### Component Imports
- Use barrel exports from `@/components` when available
- Example: `import { FadeIn, ProjectCard, ShowMoreButton } from "@/components"`
- For specific components: `import Header from "@/components/Header/Header"`

### Next.js Imports
- Use `next/link` for internal navigation
- Use `next/image` for optimized images
- Use `next/navigation` for routing utilities (notFound, etc.)

### Motion/Animation
- Import from `motion/react-client`: `import * as motion from "motion/react-client"`
- Use `motion[as]` pattern for dynamic tags: `const MotionTag = motion[as] || motion.div`

## Styling Guidelines

### SCSS Architecture
- **Variables**: Defined in `src/assets/styles/_variables.scss`
- **Mixins**: Defined in `src/assets/styles/_mixins.scss`
- **Global**: Reset and base styles in `src/assets/styles/_global.scss`
- **Component Styles**: Each component has its own `.scss` file in the same directory

### SCSS Variables Available
- **Typography**: `$font-size-*` (10, 12, 14, 16, 18, 20, 24, 28, 32, 40, 48)
- **Line Heights**: `$line-height-tight`, `$line-height-normal`, `$line-height-relaxed`
- **Font Weights**: `$fw-regular` (400), `$fw-medium` (500), `$fw-semibold` (600), `$fw-bold` (700)
- **Colors**: `$black`, `$white`, `$gray-*` (50, 100, 200, 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800, 900, 950)
- **Spacing**: `$space-*` (4, 8, 12, 16, 18, 20, 24, 32, 40)
- **Radius**: `$radius-sm`, `$radius-md`, `$radius-lg`, `$radius-xl`, `$radius-1xl`, `$radius-2xl`
- **Breakpoints**: `$breakpoint-sm` (460px), `$breakpoint-md` (778px), `$breakpoint-2md` (970px), `$breakpoint-lg` (1130px), `$breakpoint-xl` (1280px)

### SCSS Mixins Available
- `@include flex-center` - Flexbox center alignment
- `@include flex-between` - Flexbox space-between
- `@include flex-column` - Flex column direction
- `@include container` - Max-width container (740px) with padding
- `@include page` - Page layout with min-height
- `@include section` - Section styling (white background)
- `@include section-title` - Large section title styling
- `@include header_section` - Small section header badge style
- `@include next-button-style` - Button with underline hover effect

### BEM Naming Convention
- Use BEM (Block Element Modifier) for CSS classes
- Block: Component name (e.g., `project-card`)
- Element: `__element` (e.g., `project-card__title`)
- Modifier: `--modifier` (e.g., `project-card--featured`)

### Component Style Structure
```scss
@use "../../assets/styles/variables" as *;
@use "../../assets/styles/mixins" as *;

.component-name {
  // Component styles
  .component-name__element {
    // Element styles
  }
}
```

## Component Patterns

### Section Components
- Sections are in `src/sections/` directory
- Each section has its own `.jsx` and `.scss` file
- Use `FadeIn` wrapper for animations
- Use `container` class/mixin for content width
- Example structure:
```jsx
<FadeIn id="section-id" className="section-name" as="section" delay={0.3}>
  <div className="container">
    {/* Section content */}
  </div>
</FadeIn>
```

### FadeIn Component Usage
- Wrapper component for scroll animations
- Props: `id`, `className`, `as` (HTML tag), `delay`, `duration`, `direction`, `distance`, `once`
- Default: `as="div"`, `delay=0`, `duration=0.5`, `direction="up"`, `distance=30`, `once=true`
- Uses Motion library for animations

### Page Components
- Next.js pages in `src/app/` directory
- Use `page.jsx` for route pages
- Use `layout.jsx` for layout wrappers
- Dynamic routes: `[slug]/page.jsx`
- Generate static params: `generateStaticParams()` function
- Generate metadata: `generateMetadata()` function

