## Next.js Specific Patterns

### Image Optimization
- Use `next/image` component
- Provide `width` and `height` props
- Use `sizes` prop for responsive images
- Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images
- Use `priority` for above-fold images
- Support `blurDataURL` for placeholder

### Routing
- App Router structure (Next.js 13+)
- File-based routing in `src/app/`
- Dynamic routes: `[slug]/page.jsx`
- Use `Link` from `next/link` for client-side navigation
- Use `notFound()` from `next/navigation` for 404 handling

### Static Generation
- Project uses static export (`output: "export"`)
- Generate static params for dynamic routes
- Pre-render all pages at build time
- No server-side features (API routes, etc.)

## Component Export Pattern
- Barrel export file: `src/components/index.js`
- Export all reusable components from one file
- Import pattern: `import { Component1, Component2 } from "@/components"`

## Animation Guidelines
- Use `FadeIn` component for section animations
- Motion library for complex animations
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` (handled by Motion)
- Use CSS transitions for simple hover effects
- Animation delays: 0, 0.3, 0.5 seconds typically

## Accessibility Guidelines
- Use semantic HTML (`<section>`, `<article>`, `<nav>`, etc.)
- Include ARIA labels where needed
- Use `sr-only` class for screen-reader-only content
- Skip links for main content
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1 → h2 → h3)
- Alt text for all images
- Keyboard navigation support

## Performance Considerations
- Static export for fast loading
- Image optimization with Next.js Image
- Lazy loading for images below fold
- Code splitting via Next.js automatic splitting
- WebP images for better compression
- Minimal dependencies

